Tactics have always been and always will be an important part of EQ. Reso went from having KT waltzing thorugh their raid force hap-hazderly to finally executing a pinning strategy. In the past,  the RIGHT strategy, well implemented can always reduce the number of resources you need to succeed at an encounter (some folks in FnF proved that to each other late last nite). I want to define &quot;right strategy&quot; as the strategy that is best suited for your guild. Not just a strat gleamed off a board that uber guild 001 said worked for them. You say you took 42 people to Zlandicar and executed your strat flawlessly. I have no doubt you did. But was it the right strat for your raid force composition at that time? I would say no if you almost lost.<br>
