To me, the hardest part of the game is organization and motivation.  Getting people to a raid and keeping them motivated to do what's necessary to level up, gear up, and be able to get to the next encounter.  The ability to count to 4 and press a hotkey, alternate burns and concussions, or hit autoattack and keep yourself facing a mob isn't exactly brain surgery.  Getting 50 people together, organized, and moving in the same direction and keeping them together is the hard part of this game.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
