<br>
In the past some successes were based on many mods being on the ground and available. But now the fights will be shorter so less overall mana is needed thus less mod rods (if they were still available) and a shorter intense fight.<br>
<br>
Dubing the phrase &quot;Either you have it or you dont&quot;. Meaning encounters now will be based on if you can do them or not and you will know after a very short time.<br>
<br>
Wizards manaburn is a great tool and this nerf only says they cant use them in conjunction at the same time. They can still use them but now they cant kill a kunark dragon who has 32k with 6 roaming wizards. Now they MB and the dragon eats them 1 at a time. <br>
<br>
MB was nothing used by big guilds really. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Edit: Removed strat information.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I see more of a problem with them taking away MC3 but if they fix SCM as they promised this can be overcome. MC3 for those who dont know increases your inate mana regen by something like 12 points at level 3. SCM3 will reduce mana cost by 30percent if a successful roll (maybe they will make it guaranteed). So fixing SCM and maybe making it guaranteed equals 30 percent more mana when the bar is full or close to it.<br>
<br>
Cleric 7500 hp CH is nothing of a big deal either. They said this would allow them to include or allow for upgrades in the healing to this class. Imagine if you will that i have 8k hps. How often would you see me at less than 500hps on a mob that is known to hit for 1100+ per strike? Not often and even with a 10k heal this would save me if he riposted or even got another swing in. More dynamic and useful heals are coming to clerics and this will allow for more creative healing.<br>
<br>
At 7500 this will still fill up the tanks for another month and half if they were at 1 hp. When we hit VT well have more 8k tanks and by then the higher heals will be available.<br>
<br>
Monks. The only thing happening here is they are reducing the benifit to the AC + all other monkly skills. They might as well gave you all a sword + plate armor.. This is just rebalancing plate wearing classes to the front of the damage absorbsion table, nothing more and in any roleplay world an armor wearing character always take more damage than a non armor wearing one. Maybe except the Japanese Animations of Kung Fu. /shrug. There is no reason a monk cant survive pulls now. Why? cause they are fleeing and ac doesnt account from the rear only from the front so there is really no change in this aspect. The only change is you cant stand up to a mob and get beat on better than someone decked in steel protection.<br>
<br>
Perhaps raising the ability to dodge by 5 or 10 would make it better. Though i dont think your skills should be full effect if you are fleeing. You cant see them swinging how can you dodge it. Here is how I veiw a monk can be. On my old server we had a monk (guildleader) who was able to pull Ikatiar / Eashan and Roy SOLO before Luclin came out . He had perhaps 500 less hps than our lowest monk. Its all about creativity.. Not just 100khps and knowing you can run and take a 1 min break come back and still alive. There is no challenge in that.<br>
<br>
Im not advocating the changes in thier entiretly but i am saying there is nothing evident here that will change our raids. Raids will be shorter , less stressful and less time consuming. All mobs on luclin (bosses) will be expected to be reduced hps for the encounter so the time will be shorter but the mana will be similar for that short duration. <br>
<br>
Example.. Cleric uses 8k of mana for a Rhag2 fight now.. They will use 4k for a Rhag2 fight after implement and the fight will be half as long. AL who will take 15 min to kill will now take 7ish and instead of say 16k of mana will only take 8k.. this is 2 full bars of mana. Its all about scaling nothing more.<br>
